  "text": "Binding of Congo red by bacterial cells was monitored as described previously [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Briefly, O157 strains were inoculated on YESCA containing 1.5% noble agar, Congo red (40 μg/ml), coomassie brilliant blue (6.24 μg/ml) and carbenicillin (100 μg/ml). The plates were incubated at 28°C for 24-48 h. The intensity of the red color of bacterial growth produced on this medium was captured by photography.",
